# Database Selection

## RDBMS
- I can use RDBMS or NoSQL here.
- I am choosing RDBMS because we need:
  - Strong consistency
  - Transactions
  - Joins
  - Structured relationships

## NoSQL
- I am choosing NoSQL because we need:
  - Horizontal scalability
  - Flexible schema
  - Very high throughput

## Time Series DB
- I am choosing a Time Series database because:
  - Data is append-heavy
  - Queries are time-based
  - Efficient range scans and aggregations are needed

## Key-Value Store / DynamoDB
- I am choosing a key-value store because:
  - Access patterns are mostly PK lookups
  - We need predictable low latency at scale

## Wide Column DB
- I am choosing a wide-column database because:
  - We expect massive write throughput
  - Partition-based scaling is important

## Graph DB
- I am choosing a graph database because:
  - Relationships are first-class citizens
  - Traversals are important

---

# Cache

## General Cache
- I am adding cache to:
  - Reduce DB load
  - Improve read latency

## Redis
- I am using Redis because:
  - Very fast in-memory reads
  - Supports TTL
  - Supports pub/sub
  - Supports sorted sets
  - Supports atomic operations

## CDN
- I am adding CDN because:
  - Static content can be served closer to users
  - Reduces origin load
  - Improves latency globally

## Local Application Cache
- I am adding local cache because:
  - It avoids network hops
  - Frequently accessed data becomes ultra-fast

## Cache Aside
- I am using cache-aside because:
  - Application controls cache population
  - Easy eviction strategy

## Write Through Cache
- I am using write-through caching because:
  - Cache and DB stay synchronized

## Write Back Cache
- I am using write-back caching because:
  - Better for heavy writes
  - Delayed persistence is acceptable

---

# Queue / Streaming

## Message Queue
- I am adding a queue because:
  - Async processing is needed
  - Smoothens traffic spikes
  - Enables retries
  - Allows independent scaling

## Kafka
- I am choosing Kafka because:
  - Durable event streaming
  - Replay capability
  - Very high throughput
  - Partitioning support

## RabbitMQ
- I am choosing RabbitMQ because:
  - Reliable message delivery
  - Advanced routing support

## Dead Letter Queue (DLQ)
- I am adding DLQ because:
  - Failed messages can be isolated
  - Retries become easier

---

# Load Balancing

## Load Balancer
- I am adding a load balancer because:
  - Traffic distribution is needed
  - Improves availability
  - Prevents server overload

## API Gateway
- I am adding an API Gateway because:
  - Centralized authentication
  - Request routing
  - Throttling
  - Monitoring

---

# Scalability

## Horizontal Scaling
- I prefer horizontal scaling because:
  - Better fault tolerance
  - Easier scalability

## Sharding
- I am using sharding because:
  - Data distribution is needed
  - Avoids single-node bottlenecks

## Replication
- I am using replication because:
  - High availability
  - Read scalability

## Auto Scaling
- I am enabling auto scaling because:
  - Handles traffic spikes dynamically

---

# Reliability

## Retry
- I am adding retries because:
  - Helps recover from transient failures

## Circuit Breaker
- I am adding a circuit breaker because:
  - Prevents cascading failures

## Idempotency
- I am adding idempotency because:
  - Retries should not create duplicates

## Rate Limiting
- I am adding rate limiting because:
  - Protects against abuse
  - Prevents overload

## Backpressure
- I am adding backpressure because:
  - Downstream services should not get overwhelmed

---

# Consistency

## Strong Consistency
- I am choosing strong consistency because:
  - Correctness is critical

## Eventual Consistency
- I am choosing eventual consistency because:
  - Scalability and availability are prioritized

## Quorum Reads/Writes
- I am using quorum because:
  - Balances consistency and availability

---

# Search

## Elasticsearch
- I am adding Elasticsearch because:
  - Full-text search is needed
  - Fast filtering
  - Fast aggregations

## Bloom Filter
- I am adding a Bloom Filter because:
  - Prevents unnecessary DB lookups
  - Useful for non-existent keys

---

# Real-Time Communication

## WebSocket
- I am using WebSockets because:
  - Persistent bi-directional communication is needed

## SSE
- I am using SSE because:
  - Primarily server-to-client streaming

## Long Polling
- I am using long polling because:
  - Better compatibility fallback

---

# File Storage

## Object Storage
- I am using object storage because:
  - Durable
  - Cost effective
  - Ideal for large binary files

## Chunk Upload
- I am using chunk upload because:
  - Supports resumable uploads
  - Better for large files

